          BPM to present Data Science extensions for Libre Office at
          LibreOffice Conf

          Thursday, August 09, 2018 by admin

          BPM to present Data Science extensions for Libre Office at
          LibreOffice Conf   Patrick Beaucamp, Bpm-Conseil Ceo and
          Chairman will present our Data Science extension for Libre
          Office during the LibreOffice Conference in Tirana, 25-28 sept
          2018. BPM extensions make available usage of R package inside
          any spreadsheet, using the spread sheet as a dataset, as a form
          to input parameter or as a global interface to power Calc
          functions with additional R functions. The BPM development team
          has proven experience in Libre Office, through the creation of
          extensions for AklaBox, Vanilla and Data4Citizen, and the
          deployment of LibreOffice Online within AklaBox for online
          publishing of documents. For more information on our LibreOffice
          extension and how we can help you to deploy LibreOffice Online,
          please contact us at info@bpm-conseil.com

