          Vanilla Air introducing R-Tools

          Monday, May 02, 2016 by admin

          Vanilla Air introducing R-Tools Vanilla Analytics latest update
          introduced a new wizard type, R-Tools, to help developers with
          datasets recoding R-Tools is a first set of 6 functions/wizard
          to generate R code, with focus on recoding datasets : Date to
          Age Conversion : Switch a date to a number (age) … when you have
          a birthdate, you will get a number Age to Range conversion :
          From a number (age), create new classes (age range) … from a
          number, build a range New classification Group : Create new
          level in a dimension … for example : when you have country
          column and want a continent column New Calculated Column : Apply
          a calcul on a column … take an object, and apply a formula on it
          Filter Column : Filter your dataset … it will gives you a new
          dataset, filtered using your own filter Recode Column : Modify a
          column value, useful to correct wrong information in your
          dataset We are already working on adding new wizard for R code
          generation, using certified R packages. For more information on
          how we can help you with your Analytics Projects, please contact
          us at : info@bpm-conseil.com BPM Team

