          Vanilla is now Hadoop certified!

          Sunday, December 21, 2014 by paul.fresnel

          Vanilla is now Hadoop certified! Vanilla in the Big Data
          environment : after getting the Cloudera certification, Vanilla
          is now certified Hortonworks technology partner. The team has
          enlarged the platform functionalities and validated the
          Hortonworks Technology Partner certification process. Vanilla
          ETL now includes a connector for Hortonworks Platform (HDP), and
          the most used Hadoop components such HDFS, Hbase, Pig, Tez
          Mahout or Solr / Cloud, allowing you to make Big Data analysis.
          Hortonworks is leader in Apache Hadoop distribution. Its
          technological certification program examines and validates the
          best architectural practices after a series of integration
          tests, on very specific evaluation criteria taking into account
          the different possibilities of implementations. Keep in touch,
          follow our news and be the first to download the latest versions
          of the Vanilla platform ! BPM Team

